A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend an Act to amend an Act creating the board of commissioners for Cobb County,
2 Georgia, approved April 4, 1991 (Ga. L. 1991, p. 4492), as amended, so as to revise a
3 requirement for public hearings before the commission is authorized to spend over
4 $100,000.00 to employ an independent consultant or conduct an independent study; to
5 provide for other related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 An Act to amend an Act creating the board of commissioners for Cobb County, Georgia,
9 approved April 4, 1991 (Ga. L. 1991, p. 4492), as amended, is amended by revising
10 Section 11A as follows:
11 "Section 11A.
12 Before the commission expends county funds of $200,000.00 or more to employ an
13 independent consultant or consulting firm or to conduct an independent study or survey,
14 it shall hold a public hearing thereon. At least 15 days' notice of the time and place of the
15 hearing shall be published in a newspaper of general circulation in the county. Consultants
